  "prompt": "What are the top 3 biggest problems that restaurant management have with managing their waitstaff?",
  "response": "Based on industry research and feedback from restaurant managers, here are the top 3 biggest problems with managing waitstaff:\n\n1. High Employee Turnover\n- Frequent staff changes disrupt team dynamics\n- Constant training of new employees is time-consuming and expensive\n- Low wages and inconsistent schedules contribute to turnover\n- Can negatively impact service quality and customer experience\n\n2. Scheduling and Shift Coverage\n- Balancing employee availability and restaurant needs\n- Last-minute call-outs and no-shows create staffing challenges\n- Maintaining fair shift distribution\n- Complex scheduling across different roles and skill levels\n- Managing part-time and full-time staff schedules\n\n3. Performance Consistency and Training\n- Ensuring uniform service quality across all staff\n- Maintaining professional standards and customer service levels\n- Training new employees effectively\n- Motivating staff to maintain high performance\n- Addressing individual performance variations\n- Developing consistent communication and service protocols\n\nThese challenges are interconnected and can significantly impact a restaurant's operational efficiency, customer satisfaction, and overall profitability. Effective management strategies, competitive compensation, and ongoing training can help mitigate these issues.",
